        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auth): add --token flag to paste-token and surface validTypes in invalid_type warning",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #63042. Improves non-interactive auth setup and debuggability of auth profile load errors.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Adds `openclaw models auth paste-token --token <value>` for trusted scripted setup.\n- Keeps the existing interactive `paste-token` prompt when `--token` is omitted.\n- Rejects empty `--token` values before persisting credentials.\n- Validates Anthropic setup-token values before persisting them.\n- Includes accepted `validTypes` in invalid auth-profile warning logs.\n- Documents `--token` and its argv exposure tradeoff in `docs/cli/models.md`.\n- Adds an Unreleased changelog entry for the user-facing CLI fix.\n\n## Security note\n\n`--token <value>` is a convenience path for trusted shells and automation, but inline secrets can be exposed through shell history, command echoing, CI logs, or process-list tools. The CLI help and docs now say this explicitly and recommend the interactive prompt when possible.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: `models auth paste-token --token <value>` now runs through the real CLI without opening the interactive token prompt, updates the auth profile, and prints the normal config/profile update output.\n\nReal environment tested: Local checkout of PR head `57874b9b64034f7b49719067b03f29683c909b33` on 2026-05-08, running the real OpenClaw CLI through `corepack pnpm openclaw` with an isolated `OPENCLAW_HOME`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```console\n$ OPENCLAW_HOME=/private/tmp/openclaw_pr63050_home \\\n  OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/private/tmp/openclaw_pr63050_home/.openclaw \\\n  OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/private/tmp/openclaw_pr63050_home/.openclaw/openclaw.json \\\n  corepack pnpm openclaw models auth paste-token \\\n    --provider openai \\\n    --profile-id proof:manual \\\n    --token proof-redacted-token\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Copied terminal output from the real CLI command above:\n\n```console\nUpdated $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/openclaw.json\nAuth profile: proof:manual (openai/token)\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The command completed successfully without an interactive prompt and wrote the requested `proof:manual` OpenAI token auth profile in the isolated OpenClaw home.\n\nWhat was not tested: A real provider token was not used; the changed behavior under test is CLI non-interactive token ingestion and profile persistence, not provider-side authentication.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm test src/cli/models-cli.test.ts src/commands/models/auth.test.ts src/agents/auth-profiles.ensureauthprofilestore.test.ts`\n- [x] `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/cli/models-cli.ts src/commands/models/auth.ts src/agents/auth-profiles/persisted.ts src/cli/models-cli.test.ts src/commands/models/auth.test.ts src/agents/auth-profiles.ensureauthprofilestore.test.ts docs/cli/models.md CHANGELOG.md`\n- [x] `git diff --check`\n- [x] Real CLI proof above shows `models auth paste-token --token` completes without an interactive prompt.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
        "branch": "fix/63042-isolated-auth-setup",
